name: Accelerated Young
description: Young individuals (20-30 yrs) showing premature multi-organ aging (+18 years average gap). Requires early intervention.

name: Balanced Seniors
description: Senior individuals (65+ yrs) with decelerated aging (-14 years average gap). Organs appear younger than chronological age.

name: Moderate Acceleration
description: Middle-aged individuals (40-50 yrs) with slight accelerated aging (+1.7 years average gap) across multiple systems.
